OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas taken seriously, papers reveal
OL,6,FA threat to poison English water
OL,7,Fsupplies with weed killer in the late
OL,8,F1990s was taken seriously at the time
OL,9,Fby the government, according to
OL,10,Funsealed documents.
OL,12,FA group calling itself the "Republican
OL,13,FRevenge Group" sent the British
OL,14,FEmbassy a letter in 1999, threatening
OL,15,Fto introduce weed killer into
OL,16,FEngland's water supply if the
OL,17,Fgovernment did not withdraw from
OL,18,F"occupied Ireland".
