OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas taken seriously, papers reveal
OL,6,FThe group claimed the improvised
OL,7,Fchemical weapon would be attached to
OL,8,Ffire hydrants, forcing it into the
OL,9,Fwater supply and potentially poisoning
OL,10,Fhundreds of thousands of people.
OL,12,FAccording to unsealed papers, British
OL,13,Fauthorities took the threat seriously
OL,14,Fbecause the technical processes had
OL,15,Fbeen checked and were feasible.
OL,17,FThe threatening letter was also
OL,18,F"cohesive and literate" had been sent
OL,19,Fto the correct people and water
OL,20,Fauthorities in the UK, the documents
OL,21,Fsaid.
