OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas taken seriously, papers reveal
OL,6,FHowever, the British Embassy in Dublin
OL,7,Fsuspected the letter could have been a
OL,8,Ftrick by loyalists designed to smear
OL,9,Frepublicans.
OL,11,FThe potential giveaway was references
OL,12,Fto "HMG" (Her Majesty's Government)
OL,13,Fthroughout the threat, a phrase
OL,14,Funlikely to be used in earnest by a
OL,15,Frepublican.
OL,17,FThe authorities decided they had to
OL,18,Ftake the threat seriously in the
OL,19,Fcircumstances, even though it was
OL,20,Fthought the risk to life was low.
