OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas taken seriously, papers reveal
OL,6,FThe media in London, including
OL,7,FIreland's national broadcaster RTE and
OL,8,Fthe Irish newspapers, were called into
OL,9,Fa government briefing and asked not to
OL,10,Freport the story, for fear of causing
OL,11,Fpanic over what might well be a hoax.
OL,13,FThe government promised that if a real
OL,14,Fthreat was established, the public
OL,15,Fwould be informed, and said that the
OL,16,Fmedia would be told whether or not
OL,17,Fanything happened when the deadline
OL,18,Fran out.
